description: The DECEPTICONS have won, the AUTOBOTS are defeated, and the time for conquest is at hand! After finally succeeding in defeating the AUTOBOTS, the DECEPTICONS set about ruling our planet with an iron fist. Their forces invade and control New York City where, before long, they manage to cripple the United States. It's a war between the armed forces of the United States of America and a giant species of technologically advanced killing machinesa war that suddenly becomes incredibly one-sided! That is, unless the AUTOBOTS can muster their ranks and come to humanitys aid. But the way things are going on Earth, nothing short of a miracle will save the planet from utter extinction!

deck: When Goscinny started to work with Uderzo one of the their first creations was Oumpah-pah (or Ompa-pa in the English translation). Although it never reached the celebrity status of the two quirky Gauls, Asterix and Obelix, this series of albums was quite amusing and certainly belongs in the gallery of Goscinny's and Uderzo's best characters.
description:
Before Astrix and Oblix were "born", the famous French comics duo Ren Goscinny and Albert Uderzo created the present series, where we get to know the adventures of Ompa-pa, the Redskin, a prominent member of the Flatfoot tribe and his new best friend, French navy lieutenant Hubert Brussels Sprout, fondly known as Two Scalp.

In the original French, the comic was initially serialised in Journal de Tintin in 1958.

The series was translated to English by Nicholas Fry in 1977 and published in the UK by Egmont Publishing in association with Methuen.
name: Ompa-pa the Redskin

description: In the depths of the abyss, a war is being waged between the aquatic cities of Atlantis and Crozonia! Based on the Plato mythology, Atlantis was a war mongering civilization that was struck down to the bottom of the ocean by the wrath of the gods. Crozonia separated from Atlantis over five hundred years ago, and has never had a truly peaceful co-existence with its former ruler. Now Atlantis has declared war, and prepares the re-unification of the underwater world. Acaste, the princess mermaid of Crozonia is thrust into the role of leading her people. She quickly finds herself making the difficult decision of choosing between freedom and security. Matt Stark, a surface dweller caught in the middle of this battle not only witnesses this war, but may be the key to its outcome! A stranger in a strange land tale! Published by Beach Creative Studios. Created by Jim Su and Dan Merisanu. Story and Artwork by CGI veteran Jim Su. Colors by Peter Kostka and Etienne St. Laurent.
name: Crozonia

description:
Lovers Lane was a romance comic published by Lev Gleason. It was modeled on the formula behind Crime Must Pay the Penalty in order to appeal (supposedly) to a male audience as well as to women.

Begun in 1949 with issue #1 (October 1949), it ran until the the Comics Code Authority in 1954 (issue #41, June 1954). The title alone would have spelled doom under the Code, but the plot lines were often grittier than the backlash against comics would tolerate. ("Not Intended for Children", the cover warned.)

Lovers Lane was innovative in its occasional use of multi-issue storylines, and the romance was sometimes part of adventure or crime plotlines. It also had a "Dear Abby: clone, Eloise Taylor Answers Your Love Problems.
name: Lovers' Lane
